        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "for the degree of Bachelor of Science in Liberal Arts & Sciences, Major in Actuarial Science"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Departmental distinction: To qualify for distinction, the student must have a grade point average in ASRM courses of at least 3.25, and pass at least two examinations offered by the professional actuarial societies. To qualify for high or highest distinction, the student must have passed at least three professional exams, with highest distinction going to those whose grade point averages in mathematics are at least 3.75. Finance courses and additional professional exams may also be given consideration in close decisions."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Graduation Requirements"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum hours required for graduation: 120 hours.",
        "credit_requirement": "120"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum hours required major and supporting course work normally equates to 58-61 hours including 32-33 hours of actuarial courses beyond calculus. Twelve hours of 300- or 400-level courses in the major must be taken on this campus.",
        "level_requirement": "400",
        "credit_requirement": "58-61"
      },
